<p>How can I use Hlookup and vlookup with hyperlink formula in excel sheet.</p>  <p>My VlookUP function</p>  <pre><code>=VLOOKUP(A2,Lookup1, 2, FALSE)  ("idarubicin hydrochloride"[tiab] OR "57852-57-0"[rn] OR "idamycin"[tiab]) </code></pre>  <p>and my HlookUP function </p>  <pre><code>=HLOOKUP(C1,Lookup2, 2,FALSE)  ("triamcinolone acetonide"[tiab]) </code></pre>  <p>works fine.</p>  <p>I need to create dynamic hyperlink using above two lookups which should be like</p>  <pre><code>  http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=("idarubicin hydrochloride"[tiab] OR "57852-57-0"[rn] OR "idamycin"[tiab])AND("triamcinolone acetonide"[tiab]) </code></pre>  <p>I am able to use one VLOOKUP in hyperlink</p>  <pre><code>=HYPERLINK("http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term="&amp;LEFT(VLOOKUP(A2,Lookup1,2,FALSE),200),B2) </code></pre>  <p>But I also need to include HLOOKUP, how can I include that</p>